HEADWORD: Light-footed
<hw>Light"-foot`ed</hw>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a light,
springy step; moving lightly and nimbly; nimble in running or dancing;
active; <as>as, <ex>light-foot</ex> Iris</as>. Opposite of
<ant>heavy-footed</ant>.</def> <rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lightful</ent>⟦br⟧
